11. Where a registered boat is a non-decked canoe it shall be equipped
with-
     (a) an anchoring device;
     (b) at least one pair of oars;
     (c) at least one life jacket for each person to be carried thereon;
     (4 at least one cell battery operated electrical flashlight; and
     (e) at least two daylight distress flares and two night distress flares, at all
          times when such boat is in use for fishing.
